": "s"}, {"role": "present_1ms", "form": "أُسَوِّف", "in_corpus": false, "count": null, "asp": "i", "per": "1", "gen": "m", "num": "s"}, {"role": "present_1mp", "form": "نُسَوِّف", "in_corpus": false, "count": null, "asp": "i", "per": "1", "gen": "m", "num": "p"}], "frequency_in_corpus": 1, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "سَوَّفَ", "root": "", "pos": "P", "occurrence_count": 42}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 2, "pos_tags": ["particle", "verb"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 3}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n21270"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%88%D9%8E%D9%91%D9%81%D9%8E"}}, "translations": {"en": "to postpone", "fa": "به تعویق انداختن", "ur": "تأخیر کرنا", "tr": "ertelemek", "id": "menunda", "bn": "বিলম্ব করা", "es": "posponer", "fr": "remettre", "de": "verschieben", "ru": "откладывать", "zh": "推迟"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "particle", "gloss": "added to an imperfect (present) verb form to express future tense: will", "examples": [{"text": "يَقْرَأُ كِتَابًا، سَوْفَ يَقْرَأُ كِتَابًا", "english": "He is reading a book, he will read a book."}]}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to postpone, delay, procrastinate, to put off a person or thing"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to commission to, to charge", "tags": ["obsolete"]}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "Borrowed from Aramaic סוֹף / ܣܘܦ (sōp̄, “limit, end”), which was used in various adverbial uses such as “after”, “in the end”. Compare the same word pervading the Hebrew language as סוֹף (sōp̄, “end”) in later usage, and Hebrew טֶרֶם (térem, “before; not yet”) cognate to طَرْمَة (ṭarma, “upper lip; edge, protrusion”).\nFrom the Arabic particle, it was natural to form a form II verb “to put off in the future”, said of someone who commits to do something (سَوْفَ أَفْعَلُ (sawfa ʔafʕalu, “I will do”), and less well-known form I سَافَ (sāfa) meaning “to endure” and “to smell” as sensory anticipation, whence ”to hunt”, and form III سَاوِفَ (sāwifa, “to smell; to say in private; to compress, to go in unto”), and notably مَسَافَة (masāfa, “distance, interval”)."}, "ipa": null, "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n21270", "headword_ar": "سَوْفَ", "root": "swf", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ", for which one also says"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "safo", "text_ar": "سَفْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (M, Mughnee, K,) rejecting the medial radical letter, (M, Mughnee,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sawo", "text_ar": "سَوْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (M, Mughnee, K,) rejecting the final radical, (M, Mughnee,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "saYo", "text_ar": "سَىْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (M, Mughnee, K,) rejecting the final radical and changing the medial into"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Y", "text_ar": "ى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "for the purpose of alleviation [of the utterance], (M, Mughnee,) and accord. to the L"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "saA", "text_ar": "سَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (TA,) is a particle, (IJ, M, K,) denoting inception; (K;) or a word denoting"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tanofiys", "text_ar": "تَنْفِيس"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Sb, S, M, K,) i. e. amplification, because it changes the aor. from the strait time, which is the present, to the ample time, which is the future; (Mughnee voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sa", "text_ar": "سَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[q. v.];) i. e., denoting"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tnfys", "text_ar": "تنفيس"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "with respect to that which has not yet happened; (Sb, S, K;) and postponement; (M;) and is used in terrifying and threatening and promising; (IDrd, K;) or it is a word denoting promising or threatening: (Msb:) it is"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "syn. with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sa", "text_ar": "سَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "accord. to some, or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "has a larger meaning than this latter"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "accord. to others. (Mughnee.) You say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sawofa", "text_ar": "سَوْفَ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^afoEalu", "text_ar": "اَفْعَلُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I will do"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "such a thing]. (Sb, S.) And one may not introduce a separating word between it and its verb, [except in a case mentioned in what follows,] because it occupies the place of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "s", "text_ar": "س"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sayafoEalu", "text_ar": "سَيَفْعَلُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[&c.]. (Sb, S.) [But] it is distinct from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sa", "text_ar": "سَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "by its [sometimes] having"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "l", "text_ar": "ل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "prefixed to it; as in [the phrase in the Kur xciii. 5],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "walasawofa yuEoTiyka", "text_ar": "وَلَسَوْفَ يُعْطِيكَ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rab~uka fataroDaY", "text_ar": "رَبُّكَ فَتَرْضَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And thy Lord will give thee, and thou wilt be well pleased"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (Mughnee:) in this phrase, [however,] the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "l", "text_ar": "ل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is [considered as] pre-"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 1470}, {"kind": "text", "text": "fixed to the verb, not to the particle: (M:) or the phrase is elliptical, for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA^anota sawofa yuEoTiyka", "text_ar": "لَاَنْتَ سَوْفَ يُعْطِيكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Bd.) And it is distinct from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sa", "text_ar": "سَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in this, that it is sometimes separated [from its verb] by a verb divested of government both as to the letter and the meaning; as in the saying,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "wamaA A^adoriY wasawofa A_ixaAlu A^adoriY\n                      \n                     \n                        A^aqawomN A=lu HiSonK A^amo nisaA='u"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And I know not, but I shall, I think, know, whether the family of Hisn be a company of men or women"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (Mughnee.) ―         -b2-  When you desire to make it a subst., [i. e. to use it as a subst.,] you make it to have tenween [when it is indeterminate]. (IDrd, K.) IDrd cites as an ex.,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "A_in~a sawofFA waA_in~a layotFA EanaA='N"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Verily"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sawofa", "text_ar": "سَوْفَ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and verily"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "layota", "text_ar": "لَيْتَ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "are a weariness"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: but one reading is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_in~a law~FA", "text_ar": "اـِنَّ لَوًّا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and another,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_in~a layotFA", "text_ar": "اـِنَّ لَيْتًا"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wA_in~a law~FA", "text_ar": "واـِنَّ لَوًّا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and there is no such reading as"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_in~a sawofFA", "text_ar": "اـِنَّ سَوْفًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (O, TA.) One says also,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fulaAnN yaqotaAtu Als~awofa", "text_ar": "فُلَانٌ يَقْتَاتُ السَّوْفَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[lit."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Such a one feeds upon the word"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sawofa", "text_ar": "سَوْفَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; meaning (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Such a one lives by means of things hoped for:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K, TA:) and in like manner,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA quwtuhu A_il~aA Als~awofu", "text_ar": "مَا قُوتُهُ اـِلَّا السَّوْفُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[lit."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "His food is not anything but,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "other than, the word"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sawofa", "text_ar": "سَوْفَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (A, TA.) ―         -b3-  In the following verse of Ibn-Mukbil, cited by Sb,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "bisawofK mino taHiy~atihaA ↓ \n      lawo saAwafatonaA\n                      \n                     \n                        sawofa AlEayuwfi laraAHa Alr~akobu qado qaniEaA"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Had she put us off with a"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sawofa", "text_ar": "سَوْفَ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "as part of her greeting, with the putting off"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "even"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of such as is affected with dislike, the riders had gone contented"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sawofa", "text_ar": "سَوْفَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is put in the accus. case [for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "musaAwafapa", "text_ar": "مُسَاوَفَةَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", i. e.] as an inf. n. with the augmentation [meaning the augmentative letters] rejected. (M.)"}], "source_refs": ["TA", "IJ", "M", "K", "Sb", "S", "Msb"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}